cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes an architecture based on Autoencoders for the task of Matrix Completion in Recommender Systems. It also involves the use of loss functions and side information, which are common techniques in Machine Learning. 

It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as Recommender Systems are often used in Information Retrieval applications. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category as the paper proposes a method for inferring unknown ratings in Recommender Systems, which is a common task in AI. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely sub-category, but it could be relevant as the paper deals with the problem of completing a partially known matrix of ratings, which involves handling and manipulating data structures. 

Finally, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible sub-category as Recommender Systems are often used in social networks and involve analyzing user behavior and preferences.
